Encapsulating the anthocyanin into nanoparticles plays a significant role in overcoming this drawback and improving their antiviral properties (
 Amin et al., 2017; 
 Ahsan et al., 2018). Protein encapsulation of procyanidins could attenuate their degradation under ultraviolet and other stressful conditions. According to Liu et al., nanocrystallization of anthocyanin potentiated the antioxidant capacity of pure proanthocyanidins under stressful conditions (
 Liu et al., 2017). These all clarify the critical role of nanocrystallization-induced improvement in the stability of anthocyanins (
 Arroyo-Maya and McClements, 2015; 
 Zhang et al., 2019).
